              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top" width="100" nowrap><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><b>Gannun</b></font></td>
                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top" width="100%"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;01/16/2004&nbsp;: 01:43:06 AM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> Basically I tried to post why we don't twitch, using the math, here's the post and here's the last reply:<br /><br />MY POST:<br /><br />kk, this is to clarify why I don't twitch during raid mobs, and that i do actually know what i'm talking about and know how to play my class properly.... I dug out some old maths from the necro boards:<br /><br />verser parsed the idol at 835 dps. the fight lasted 4:31. we healed 226,481 hp. my mana pool is 3300, and i regen mana at 35(al)+7(sp)+7(ft)+13(bard)=62/tick standing. the fight lasted 45 ticks, so i would regen 2790 mana during that time, making my available mana pool for the fight 6090. <br /><br />case 1: twitchin:<br />so let's say i spend all my mana twitching cause i wanna be a team player. both twitch spells are roughly a 3:1 ratio, so assuming i get some decent rolls on spec i can transfer ~3000 mana in that time (due to the total cast time, i.e. recast aswell ,of twitch being 11seconds). let's also pretend that i spread it out perfectly across the ch chain. I believe the chain was set to ch every 2 seconds, so assuming that ch actually costs each cleric about 300 (i'll be generous) mana to cast after spec checks, that's 10 more ch's that can land before they run outa mana. the ma will live an additional 20 seconds because i'm a battery. <br /><br />for the sake of argument, let's say that the idol had just enough hp to make those 20 seconds the difference in the fight, and he dies and we all are oom at the exacty time he eats it. so twitching was a good idea right? let's see. <br /><br />verser has the idol taking 200k in melee damage during that 4:31, and for the sake of argument let's not take the nukers into account, since we can't really judge what their output was, and it would only correspondingly raise the idol's hp in our little example here. i'm pretty sure we can get away with it without breaking our example, which leads us to: <br /><br />case 2: snag does damage:<br /><br />6090 mana for a 4:31 fight. <br /><br />4 funeral pyres in 4 minutes: 2160X4 = 8640 for 1800 mana (it's alteration so we'll call it 1500)<br /><br />3 splurts in 4:30: 4800 for 711 mana (also alt, so we'll say 500)<br /><br />2 pyrocurors in 4 minutes: 4k damage for 800 mana (alt, we'll say 600)<br /><br />4 cessation of cor's in 4 min: 4k damage for 1k mana (alt, 800 mana)<br /><br />vexing mordania 2x over that time: 2k damage for 1k mana, (alt, 800 mana)<br /><br />let's see, that brings dot damage up to: <br /><br />23,440 damage for 4200 mana, leaving almost 3k mana for nukes: <br />4x touch of night (average ~800)= 3200 for about 1400 mana, 1600 not counting specs. <br /><br />so let's call that close enough, and see how much shorter the idol's life would have been without that extra 26,640 hp. <br /><br />the fight lasted 271 seconds, and we did 195,161 damage to him in that time. this puts our dps at 720 (assuming dps is damage/seconds)... again it's actually higher than that, but so is the true value of the hp damage we did to it, so they should cancel each other out. <br /><br />assuming my math is right, it would have taken us an extra 37 seconds to make up for the damage i theoretically did. pretty obviously, my dps is worth twice as much as my twitching. I would rather have a fight last 37 seconds shorter than baseline rather than extend a fight for 20 seconds but have to make up for all my lost damage. this goes doubly for any fight where we have to worry about healing rampage tanks, ae damage, or any other kind of non-ma damage. higher dps = shorter fights = better for everyone. <br /><br />so you see, long fights are no different than any other. twitch is massively, horribly, and unspeakably mana-inefficient. i know it sounds good on paper that being able to heal for a tiny bit longer is best for the encounter, but it obviously isn't. <br /><br />and don't forget my original point, that mind wrack creates mana out of nothing, actually gives each necro doing it more mana than it costs, and is easy done. to give a quickie comparison: <br /><br />twitch: ~3k mana delivered with a 8 second dly recast time spell over 4:31. <br /><br />mind wrack: 9 casts of mw, each netting 300 mana for every person in group: 2700 x 6 = 24,300 mana &lt;--- not a typo. and it's *free*. i can do all my dps i want while doing it, and so can all the other necros. <br /><br />it's a fallacy to think that twitching is anything but a bad idea in most situations outside of buff/coh cycles. it's silly to poo-poo a necro's dps because 'cleric mana' has a mystique of being more important. <br /><br />Unless i've made some gross math error, necro dps is much more useful than our pitiful 3:1 ratio twitches.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Now this was taken on a lvl 60 necro..... i'm 65 and can produce much more damage than he has produced there, therefore the damage to twitch ratio is even worse....<br /><br />This parse basically shows how much more effective a necro is at shortening a fight compared to extending it... which as he said helps also with non MT damage (i.e. ramp etc). It's comparable to all the melee in a raid bindwounding the MT lol. (Sinthel likes that example so thought i'd stick it in  )<br /><br />Some of you may also say that I can regen enough mana to sustain my DPS aswell as twitching in between DoT casts.... I would agree except for the fact that 'im permanantly casting one spell or another. If I have all my DoTs running i'll FD and nuke a couple then FD nuke a couple more, then a dot will wear so ill reapply, FD etc etc.<br /><br />Obviously twitch is a tool, a situational tool. I will gladly twitch for buffing and coth etc. I will also twitch someone if they have just died and they are a key class in the raid i.e. chanter goes down doing CC, they get rezzed and i'll twitch em up so they got enough mana to get back to doing CC. Or if the mob is resistant to nearly all my spells lol.<br /><br />Theres other situations that come up where i'll think to myself yea I need to twitch here, but I can decide that cos I know when its best to twitch and best not too... I know my class very well. Also I do not tell other people how to play their class, this is one of the things that nagged me a little. I trust everyone in our guild enough to know that they know what they are doing, please give me the same credit, tis all i ask  <br /><br />Hope this clears things up  <br /><br /><br />P.S. And yes Guno  if I die this all goes out the window lol  <br />But if I die its cos im slacking and not watching my aggro... same as if any other DPS class dies hehe.<br /><br /><br /><br />REPLY:<br /><br />Gannun i am sorry but if this what you base your argument on then it's very wrong.<br />First this guy math is 2 years old and like i told you his math is even more wrong becouse he base it on the fact that all clerics mana pools are the same.<br />Here is how the math should be seen<br />we fight Mobs X, the mob can quad up to 1k 4 times per tick for a MAX dps of 2.6k please notice it's the max DPS we need to heal not the REAL DPS <br />Our uber tank have 9k HP.<br />So to counter the mob we we need to land a CH every 2 sec (the math is that a MA should NOT get below 40% life anyware during the fight otherwise every time a cleric lag a little we have a dead MA) so we need to run a chain assumeing MA have 5.4k and that goes to about 1 CH each 2 sec, now at this point i will assume the chain is PERFECT there is no delay between the clerics so wwe only need to use 6 clerics (normaly for such mobs we will use at lease 7 clerics with a backup CCH of druid like MM).<br />Let's assume cleric 1-4 have 5000 mana pool FT15 MC3 have all the buffs total mana regen is (16+15+3+9+ 51<br />We also have two clerics with 