                <td bgcolor="#3C4884" valign="top"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;01/16/2004&nbsp;: 02:34:00 AM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> Original post has unrealistic assumptions, such as, that the necro can output 40% of the raids dps if he used his mana for damage.  Everything past that is garbage.<br /><br />Twtich transfer factoids<br />Sedulous Subversion Base cost: 400 mana<br />   200 Alteration - -10%<br />   Conservation of Xegony (1-20) -10.5%<br />   SCM3 - 10%<br />Actual Mana cost: 278 mana<br />Transfers: 150 mana<br />Transfer Ratio 1.85 to 1<br /><br />Complete Heal Spell: Base cost 400 mana<br />     Alteration 200 -10%<br />     SCM3 - 10%<br />     Think CH is excluded from every focus on mana preservation<br />Actual Mana cost: 320<br /><br /><b>So it effectively costs the necro 592 mana to complete heal someone.</b><br /><br />Now lets assume the clerics are using a CH chain...2 seconds seems pretty standard, its been said no mob in the game requires a truly 1 second CH chain.  Now lets say that you twitched the weak link in this chain. For every 592 mana you spend, they receive 320 mana which is enough for them to cast another CH.  So every 592 mana you send someone the CH chain continues to function, and the death and carnage of the MT dying is delayed 2 seconds longer....<br /><br />Now, what is a reasonable dps for an entire raid nowadays?  Don't time gods have at least 1million hp? Nummies guild killed them in 3.8 minutes by her parse, making a raid dps of about 4500 (If anyone knows actually how much hp a PoT god has, particularly tallon zek, plz post, and i'll edit this part).  So, by sacrifcing 592 mana, you effectively allow the raid to function 2 seconds longer, creating 9000 additional damage.  <b> 9000/592 = 15 Damage to mana ratio, a better damage to mana ratio than <u> any necro dot.</u> </b><br /><br />For those necros arguing that twitching is inefficient you need to come up with a better argument.  Now granted, if your a necro and dpsing, a shorter fight, less can go wrong, this is a valid point.  It is also a valid point that necros are not the only source of mana.  But if your healers are going OOM to soon to win the fight, using the twtich spell can easily swing the difference.  That being said, its a gimp tactic, as lame as mages pooping mod rods, and I wish the twitch spells didn't exist.  Because twitch = somebody else playing with your mana, and you medding, is not fun.<br /><br /></span></font></td>
